</IN>
<LP>
   PARIS -- Rhone-Poulenc S.A. agreed to sell a citric acid
plant in the U.K. to Haarman &amp; Reimer, a unit of Bayer AG of
West Germany, for #56 million ($100.8 million).
   The French state-owned chemical and pharmaceutical group
said the agreement is subject to the approval of the
authorities.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Rhone-Poulenc acquired the Selby facility when it took
over the chemical activities of RTZ PLC in 1989. The facility
was inaugurated at the beginning of this year and has a
capacity of 23,000 tons.
</TEXT>
